Class LexicalElement_Type

java.lang.Object
org.apache.uima.jcas.cas.TOP_Type
org.apache.uima.jcas.cas.AnnotationBase_Type

gov.va.chir.model.LexicalElement_Type
Direct Known Subclasses:
Acronym_Type, AcronymExpansion_Type, Organization_Type, PersonalName_Type, Shape_Type
public class LexicalElement_Type
extends VAnnotation_Type
Lexical Element is a container class for the terms of a document. A term is a word or words that equate to what you'd find in a dictionary. This includes both single and multi-token items such as "a priori". This class also includes multiple tokens that wouldn't be covered in a dictionary like dates, times, phone numbers, urls, and identifiers. Updated by JCasGen Wed Aug 17 13:31:49 EDT 2022
